–The attending anesthetist should be aware of the indications and the difference between lung separation and isolation. This definition has replaced the historical classification of absolute and relative indications of one-lung ventilation (Table 4
).–In general, 95.2% of the respondents to the survey have reported that they would use a bronchial blocker (BB), and 47.6 % a double-lumen tube (DLT) in patient with, or suspected to have COVID-19, The sum is > 100% as some members advocated the possible use of both devices for different indications (Figure 2
).–The use of BB for all patients is advocated by 52.4%; 33.3% would use BB in already intubated patients, and 9.5% in patients with difficult airway. Conversely, 28.6% would use DLT in all cases, and 19% only in non-intubated cases (Figure 3
).
